`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- `getEffectiveTradeRate` is a pure transform: apply the supply/demand multiplier for the *output* resource to the `toAmount`. This follows the spec formula `effectiveRate = baseRate × supplyDemandMultiplier`.
- Keeping supply/demand computation in GameUI (not in TradeDialog) follows separation of concerns — the dialog just renders what it receives, the orchestrator owns the business logic.
- The `marketState.priceMultipliers` field is already kept up-to-date by `recordTrade` on every trade — no extra computation step needed at read time.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
