`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `Modal → absolute View` conversion reveals a key FPS HUD principle: system modals create a separate rendering context above the game canvas, while absolute Views stay in the React tree and compose naturally with other HUD layers (weather, radial menus, etc.).
- `marketState.priceMultipliers` is a derived cache maintained by `recordTrade()` — always up-to-date, making it safe to use directly without re-computing on every render.
